<span id="freeTextContainer11129834499235641263">A third-person autobiography, <i> The Education of Henry Adams </i> is unlike anything I&apos;ve ever read before. Adams does not come across as especially insightful or even particularly likeable, but I found myself compelled to keep reading. It&apos;s a fascinating picture of our country at the turn of the 20th century.</span>
